Uses of Package
mainPackage

  • Classes in mainPackage used by mainPackage 
    Class and Description
    CannotMoveIntoWallsException
    The class CannotMoveIntoWallsException it is a throwable exception, that can be thrown when the hero tries to go through a wall.
    Cell
    Cell class represents a cell inside of a maze, that can be a wall, a portal such as enter portal or exit portal, or the roads of the maze.
    CellFactory
    CellFactory class implements a singleton and a factory design pattern, used to create new cells for maze, using a string as identifier.
    Direction
    Direction enum represents the direction of the next cell where the hero will go, or the direction where it is a cell according to the position of the hero.
    Hero
    Hero class represent a hero that wants to solve a maze.
    Hero.NeighborCell
    NeighborCell class has data about a cell like a reference to that cell and the direction/orientation where the cell may be found.
    HeroOutOfGroundException
    The class HeroOutOfGroundException it is a throwable exception, that can be thrown when the hero tries to leave the playground, going to a cell that is outside of the border.
    Maze
    Maze class reprezents a board of cells that have some properties like wall cells or free cells.
    Orientation
    Orientation enum represents the four cardinal directions: EAST, NORTH, WEST, SOUTH.
    PathCell
    The abstract class PathCell it is used to identify cells where hero can stay.
    Position
    Position class represents the coordinates of a cell on the maze board.
